&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Architect and oversee&lt;/strong&gt; the high-level design of gameplay animation systems, ensuring scalability, performance, and seamless integration across complex real-time systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Drive R&amp;amp;D initiatives&lt;/strong&gt; to evaluate and implement cutting-edge animation technologies (e.g., advanced Motion Matching, machine learning/AI animation, next-gen physics).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Partner with Engineering and Tech Animation leadership&lt;/strong&gt; to implement project-wide animation roadmaps and toolsets.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Solve deep, complex runtime bugs&lt;/strong&gt; and drive animation optimisation efforts to meet strict performance and memory budgets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Define and document&lt;/strong&gt; technical standards, best practices, and pipeline workflows for the wider technical animation team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Collaborate closely with Design and Animation leads&lt;/strong&gt; to heavily iterate on and perfect 3C mechanics (character, camera, controls), maximizing game feel.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Actively mentor and upskill&lt;/strong&gt; senior and mid-level technical animators through code/blueprint reviews and hands-on guidance.&lt;/li&gt;
